						<summary>

						<p>Slab built into the southern side of the platform of the Chennakēśava temple.</p>						

						<p>Sadāśiva, 1553 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 147[5] Pramādicha, Bhādrapada ba.</hi></p>						

						<p>Damaged and incomplete. Seems to record a gift to god Chennakēśvara of Śivanūru <hi rend="italic">lias</hi> Tiruvēṁgaḷa-Nellūru by Sāḷuva Lakshmayya, Sāḷuva Bukkarāju, Sāḷuva Timayya, Kaṭhāri Bairāju and some other members of the Dommari (acrobat) community, who offered their obeisance to the deity.</p>						

						</summary>
